                "caption": "Table 7:Detailed dataset-level preference accuracy of extant RMs and theThemis-RMsuite on theFunctional Correctness (FC)split ofThemis-CodeRewardBench. Observe the marked drop in performance of extant RMs at judging partially correct solutions (MBPP+Fix (Hard)) as well as on open-domain GitHub commit preferences (CommitPref). For a detailed discussion of comparative results and the split-level average, refer toSection˜5.1. Refer toSection˜5.2for experiments on how RMs trained on functional preferences fare when tested on non-functional preferences.",
