                "caption": "Table 8:Detailed dataset-level preference accuracy of extant RMs and theThemis-RMsuite on theExecution Efficiency (EE)andMemory Efficiency (ME)splits ofThemis-CodeRewardBench. Observe how most extant scalar RMs degenerate to near random performance on non-functional criteria and how the low-resolution scoring of generative RMs can render them unusable in such settings. For a detailed discussion of comparative results and the split-level averages, refer toSection˜5.1. Refer toSection˜5.2for experiments on how RMs trained on functional preferences fare when tested on non-functional preferences.",
